 216 Generalized·Ufuncs
 217 ==================
  
 218 The·``numba.vectorize``·module·also·provides·support·for·generalized·ufuncs.
 219 Traditional·ufuncs·perfom·element-wise·operations,·whereas·generalized·ufuncs·operate·on·entire
 220 sub-arrays.·Unlike·other·Numba·Vectorize·classes,·the·GUVectorize·constructor·takes
 221 an·additional·signature·which·specifies·the·shapes·of·the·inner·arrays·we·want·to·operate·on.
  
 222 Imports
 223 -------
  
 224 ::
  
 225 ····from·numba·import·float32,·float64,·int32
 226 ····from·numba.vectorize·import·GUVectorize
 227 ····import·numpy·as·np
  
 228 Generalized·ufunc·Definition
 229 ----------------------------
  
 230 GUVectorize·ufunc·arguments·are·vectors·of·a·NumPy·array.··Function·definitions·can·be·arbitrary
 231 expressions.
  
 232 ::
  
 233 ····def·matmulcore(A,·B,·C):
 234 ········m,·n·=·A.shape
 235 ········n,·p·=·B.shape
 236 ········for·i·in·range(m):
 237 ············for·j·in·range(p):
 238 ················C[i,·j]·=·0
 239 ················for·k·in·range(n):
 240 ····················C[i,·j]·+=·A[i,·k]·*·B[k,·j]
  
 241 Compilation·requires·type·information.·Numba·assumes·no·knowledge·of·type·when·building·native
 242 ufuncs.·We·must·therefore·define·argument·and·return·dtypes·for·the·defined·ufunc.·We·can·add
 243 as·many·dtypes·as·we·need,·which·do·not·need·to·be·uniform,·i.e.·we·can·specify·a·gufunc
 244 taking·an·array·of·ints·and·an·array·of·doubles·while·producing·an·array·of·complex·numbers.
 245 The·``gufunc``·will·dispatch·to·the·right·implementation·depending·on·the·argument·types.
  
 246 We·can·define·our·gufunc·as·follows:
  
 247 ::
  
 248 ····gufunc·=·GUVectorize(matmulcore,·'(m,n),(n,p)->(m,p)')
 249 ····gufunc.add(argtypes=[float32[:,:],·float32[:,:],·float32[:,:]])
 250 ····gufunc.add(argtypes=[float64[:,:],·float64[:,:],·float64[:,:]])
 251 ····gufunc.add(argtypes=[int32[:,:],·int32[:,:],·int32[:,:]])
  
 252 Above·we·are·using·a·float·**float32**,·a·double·**float64**,·and·a·signed·**32-bit·int**.··The
 253 GUVectorize·calls·`PyDynUFunc_FromFuncAndDataAndSignature
 254 <http://scipy-lectures.github.com/advanced/advanced_numpy/index.html#generalized-ufuncs>`_·which
 255 requires·a·the·signature:·*(m,n),(n,p)->(m,p)*·in·the·constructor.··This·signature·defines·the·*"core
 256 dimensions"*·of·the·generalized·ufunc.
  
 257 We·can·compile·the·ufunc·as·follows:
  
 258 ::
  
 259 ····gufunc·=·gufunc.build_ufunc()
  
 260 We·can·now·use·the·gufunc·with·two·NumPy·matrices:
  
 261 ::
  
 262 ····matrix_ct·=·10
 263 ····A·=·np.arange(matrix_ct·*·2·*·4,·dtype=np.float32).reshape(matrix_ct,·2,·4)
 264 ····B·=·np.arange(matrix_ct·*·4·*·5,·dtype=np.float32).reshape(matrix_ct,·4,·5)
 265 ····C·=·gufunc(A,·B)
  
  
 266 Notice·that·we·don't·have·a·third·argument·in·the·gufunc·call·but·the·generalized·ufunc·definition
 267 above·has·three·arguments.·The·last·argument·of·the·generalized·ufunc·is·the·output,·which·is
 268 automatically·allocated·with·the·shape·specified·in·the·signature.

92 Each·IR·consists·of·two·layers,·namely·a·higher-level·Abstract·Syntax·Tree 
93 encoding,·specified,·verified·and·generated·by·our·variant·of·ASDL 
94 schemas.·We·add·the·symbol·``@``·to·signal·that·the·given·type 
95 is·to·be·treated·as·a·"unique"·object,·i.e.·one·that·compares·by·identity 
96 as·opposed·to·structural·equality.·These·objects·each·carry·a·unique·id 
97 and·are·serialized·in·a·table·(and·they·may·participate·in·circular 
98 references,·i.e.·in·a·graph): 
  
99 Serialization·to·LLVM·IR·(or·a·direct·textual·serialization)·will 
100 consist·of·something·like·a·generated·table,·e.g. 
  
101 ..·code-block::·pycon 
  
102 ····>>>·mod·=·schema.parse("foo·=·@Foo(str·name,·foo·attr)") 
  
103 ····>>>·foo1·=·mod.Foo("foo1") 
104 ····>>>·foo2·=·mod.Foo("foo2",·foo1) 
105 ····>>>·foo1.attr·=·foo2 
  
106 ····>>>·foo1 
107 ····Foo(name="foo1",·attr=Foo("foo2",·Foo(name="foo1",·attr=...))) 
  
108 ····>>>·build_llvm_ir(foo1)···#·name,··id,····attr 
109 ····!0·=·metadata·!{·metadata·!"foo1",·i64·0,·i64·1·} 
110 ····!1·=·metadata·!{·metadata·!"foo2",·i64·1,·i64·0·} 
  
111 Attributes·may·also·be·hidden·using·``\``,·which·means·the·attribute 
112 is·not·considered·a·child·for·the·purposes·of·visitors·or·term 
113 rewrites:: 
  
114 ····foo·=·@Foo(str·name,·foo·\attr) 
  
115 Use·of·Schemas 
116 -------------- 
117 We·can·use·our·schemas·to: 
  
118 ····*·Validate·IR·instances 
119 ····*·Generate·Python·AST·classes·with·typed·properties·and·fast 
120 ······visitor·dispatching 
121 ····*·Generate·Higher-·or·Lower-level·LLVM·IR 
122 ····*·Generate·conversion·code·to·and·from·an·ATerm·representation 
123 ····*·Generate·a·flat·representation.·E.g.·a·form·of·Three·Address·Code 
124 ····*·Generate·an·implementation·in·other·languages·that·can·load·a 
125 ······serialized·representation·and·construct·an·AST·in·that·langauge 
126 ····*·Generate·type·definitions·and·serialization·routines·in 
127 ······other·languages.
